window.BIBLE["Malachi"] = {"1":{"chapter":"1","title":"I HAVE LOVED JACOB","verses":{"1":{"text":"The burden of the word of the LORD to Israel by Malachi.","ref":"Malachi 1:1","synthesized":"This is the burden of the word of the LORD to Israel through Malachi:","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The burden of the word of the LORD to Israel by Malachi."},"BSB":{"text":"This is the burden of the word of the LORD to Israel through Malachi:"},"TANAKH":{"text":"THE BURDEN of the word of HaShem to Israel by Malachi."},"HEBREW":{"text":"מַשָּׂ֥א דְבַר־יְהוָ֖ה אֶל־יִשְׂרָאֵ֑ל בְּיַ֖ד מַלְאָכִֽי׃"}},"definableWords":["word","LORD","Israel"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"I have loved you, saith the LORD. Yet ye say, Wherein hast thou loved us? Was not Esau Jacob’s brother? saith the LORD: yet I loved Jacob,","ref":"Malachi 1:2","synthesized":"“I have loved you,” says the LORD.  But you ask, “How have You loved us?”  “Was not Esau Jacob’s brother?” declares the LORD. “Yet Jacob I have loved,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"I have loved you, saith the LORD. Yet ye say, Wherein hast thou loved us? Was not Esau Jacob’s brother? saith the LORD: yet I loved Jacob,"},"BSB":{"text":"“I have loved you,” says the LORD.  But you ask, “How have You loved us?”  “Was not Esau Jacob’s brother?” declares the LORD. “Yet Jacob I have loved,"},"TANAKH":{"text":"I have loved you, saith HaShem. Yet ye say: 'Wherein hast Thou loved us?' Was not Esau Jacob's brother? saith HaShem; yet I loved Jacob;"},"HEBREW":{"text":"אָהַ֤בְתִּי אֶתְכֶם֙ אָמַ֣ר יְהוָ֔ה וַאֲמַרְתֶּ֖ם בַּמָּ֣ה אֲהַבְתָּ֑נוּ הֲלוֹא־אָ֨ח עֵשָׂ֤ו לְיַֽעֲקֹב֙ נְאֻם־יְהוָ֔ה וָאֹהַ֖ב אֶֽת־יַעֲקֹֽב׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD","Esau","Jacob","brother","Lord"],"peopleInVerse":["Esau","Jacob"]},"3":{"text":"And I hated Esau, and laid his mountains and his heritage waste for the dragons of the wilderness.","ref":"Malachi 1:3","synthesized":"but Esau I have hated, and I have made his mountains a wasteland and left his inheritance to the desert jackals.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And I hated Esau, and laid his mountains and his heritage waste for the dragons of the wilderness."},"BSB":{"text":"but Esau I have hated, and I have made his mountains a wasteland and left his inheritance to the desert jackals.”"},"TANAKH":{"text":"But Esau I hated, and made his mountains a desolation, and gave his heritage to the jackals of the wilderness."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְאֶת־עֵשָׂ֖ו שָׂנֵ֑אתִי וָאָשִׂ֤ים אֶת־הָרָיו֙ שְׁמָמָ֔ה וְאֶת־נַחֲלָת֖וֹ לְתַנּ֥וֹת מִדְבָּֽר׃"}},"definableWords":["Esau","made"],"peopleInVerse":["Esau"]},"4":{"text":"Whereas Edom saith, We are impoverished, but we will return and build the desolate places; thus saith the LORD of hosts, They shall build, but I will throw down; and they shall call them, The border of wickedness, and, The people against whom the LORD hath indignation for ever.","ref":"Malachi 1:4","synthesized":"Though Edom may say, “We have been devastated, but we will rebuild the ruins,” this is what the LORD of Hosts says: “They may build, but I will demolish. They will be called the Land of Wickedness, and a people with whom the LORD is indignant forever.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Whereas Edom saith, We are impoverished, but we will return and build the desolate places; thus saith the LORD of hosts, They shall build, but I will throw down; and they shall call them, The border of wickedness, and, The people against whom the LORD hath indignation for ever."},"BSB":{"text":"Though Edom may say, “We have been devastated, but we will rebuild the ruins,” this is what the LORD of Hosts says: “They may build, but I will demolish. They will be called the Land of Wickedness, and a people with whom the LORD is indignant forever."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Whereas Edom saith: 'We are beaten down, but we will return and build the waste places'; thus saith HaShem of hosts: They shall build, but I will throw down; and they shall be called The border of wickedness, and The people whom HaShem execrateth for ever."},"HEBREW":{"text":"כִּֽי־תֹאמַ֨ר אֱד֜וֹם רֻשַּׁ֗שְׁנוּ וְנָשׁוּב֙ וְנִבְנֶ֣ה חֳרָב֔וֹת כֹּ֤ה אָמַר֙ יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֔וֹת הֵ֥מָּה יִבְנ֖וּ וַאֲנִ֣י אֶהֱר֑וֹס וְקָרְא֤וּ לָהֶם֙ גְּב֣וּל רִשְׁעָ֔ה וְהָעָ֛ם אֲשֶׁר־זָעַ֥ם יְהוָ֖ה עַד־עוֹלָֽם׃"}},"definableWords":["Edom","LORD","land","people","Lord"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"5":{"text":"And your eyes shall see, and ye shall say, The LORD will be magnified from the border of Israel.","ref":"Malachi 1:5","synthesized":"You will see this with your own eyes, and you yourselves will say, ‘The LORD is great—even beyond the borders of Israel.’”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And your eyes shall see, and ye shall say, The LORD will be magnified from the border of Israel."},"BSB":{"text":"You will see this with your own eyes, and you yourselves will say, ‘The LORD is great—even beyond the borders of Israel.’”"},"TANAKH":{"text":"And your eyes shall see, and ye shall say: 'The HaShem is great beyond the border of Israel.'"},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְעֵינֵיכֶ֖ם תִּרְאֶ֑ינָה וְאַתֶּ֤ם תֹּֽאמְרוּ֙ יִגְדַּ֣ל יְהוָ֔ה מֵעַ֖ל לִגְב֥וּל יִשְׂרָאֵֽל׃"}},"definableWords":["see","LORD","great","Israel"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"6":{"text":"A son honoureth his father, and a servant his master: if then I be a father, where is mine honour? and if I be a master, where is my fear? saith the LORD of hosts unto you, O priests, that despise my name. And ye say, Wherein have we despised thy name?","ref":"Malachi 1:6","synthesized":"“A son honors his father, and a servant his master. But if I am a father, where is My honor? And if I am a master, where is your fear of Me?” says the LORD of Hosts to you priests who despise My name.  “But you ask, ‘How have we despised Your name?’","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"A son honoureth his father, and a servant his master: if then I be a father, where is mine honour? and if I be a master, where is my fear? saith the LORD of hosts unto you, O priests, that despise my name. And ye say, Wherein have we despised thy name?"},"BSB":{"text":"“A son honors his father, and a servant his master. But if I am a father, where is My honor? And if I am a master, where is your fear of Me?” says the LORD of Hosts to you priests who despise My name.  “But you ask, ‘How have we despised Your name?’"},"TANAKH":{"text":"A son honoureth his father, and a servant his master; if then I be a father, where is My honour? and if I be a master, where is My fear? saith HaShem of hosts unto you, O priests, that despise My name. And ye say: 'Wherein have we despised Thy name?'"},"HEBREW":{"text":"בֵּ֛ן יְכַבֵּ֥ד אָ֖ב וְעֶ֣בֶד אֲדֹנָ֑יו וְאִם־אָ֣ב אָ֣נִי אַיֵּ֣ה כְבוֹדִ֡י וְאִם־אֲדוֹנִ֣ים אָנִי֩ אַיֵּ֨ה מוֹרָאִ֜י אָמַ֣ר ׀ יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֗וֹת לָכֶם֙ הַכֹּֽהֲנִים֙ בּוֹזֵ֣י שְׁמִ֔י וַאֲמַרְתֶּ֕ם בַּמֶּ֥ה בָזִ֖ינוּ אֶת־שְׁמֶֽךָ׃"}},"definableWords":["son","father","servant","Father","fear","LORD","name"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"7":{"text":"Ye offer polluted bread upon mine altar; and ye say, Wherein have we polluted thee? In that ye say, The table of the LORD is contemptible.","ref":"Malachi 1:7","synthesized":"By presenting defiled food on My altar.  But you ask, ‘How have we defiled You?’  By saying that the table of the LORD is contemptible.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Ye offer polluted bread upon mine altar; and ye say, Wherein have we polluted thee? In that ye say, The table of the LORD is contemptible."},"BSB":{"text":"By presenting defiled food on My altar.  But you ask, ‘How have we defiled You?’  By saying that the table of the LORD is contemptible."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Ye offer polluted bread upon Mine altar. And ye say: 'Wherein have we polluted thee?' In that ye say: 'The table of HaShem is contemptible.'"},"HEBREW":{"text":"מַגִּישִׁ֤ים עַֽל־מִזְבְּחִי֙ לֶ֣חֶם מְגֹאָ֔ל וַאֲמַרְתֶּ֖ם בַּמֶּ֣ה גֵֽאַלְנ֑וּךָ בֶּאֱמָרְכֶ֕ם שֻׁלְחַ֥ן יְהוָ֖ה נִבְזֶ֥ה הֽוּא׃"}},"definableWords":["altar","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"8":{"text":"And if ye offer the blind for sacrifice, is it not evil? and if ye offer the lame and sick, is it not evil? offer it now unto thy governor; will he be pleased with thee, or accept thy person? saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 1:8","synthesized":"When you offer blind animals for sacrifice, is it not wrong? And when you present the lame and sick ones, is it not wrong? Try offering them to your governor! Would he be pleased with you or show you favor?” asks the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And if ye offer the blind for sacrifice, is it not evil? and if ye offer the lame and sick, is it not evil? offer it now unto thy governor; will he be pleased with thee, or accept thy person? saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"When you offer blind animals for sacrifice, is it not wrong? And when you present the lame and sick ones, is it not wrong? Try offering them to your governor! Would he be pleased with you or show you favor?” asks the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"And when ye offer the blind for sacrifice, is it no evil! And when ye offer the lame and sick, is it no evil! Present it now unto thy governor; will he be pleased with thee? or will he accept thy person? saith HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְכִֽי־תַגִּשׁ֨וּן עִוֵּ֤ר לִזְבֹּ֙חַ֙ אֵ֣ין רָ֔ע וְכִ֥י תַגִּ֛ישׁוּ פִּסֵּ֥חַ וְחֹלֶ֖ה אֵ֣ין רָ֑ע הַקְרִיבֵ֨הוּ נָ֜א לְפֶחָתֶ֗ךָ הֲיִּרְצְךָ֙ א֚וֹ הֲיִשָּׂ֣א פָנֶ֔יךָ אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["sacrifice","offering","or","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"And now, I pray you, beseech God that he will be gracious unto us: this hath been by your means: will he regard your persons? saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 1:9","synthesized":"“But ask now for God’s favor. Will He be gracious? Since this has come from your hands, will He show you favor?” asks the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And now, I pray you, beseech God that he will be gracious unto us: this hath been by your means: will he regard your persons? saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"“But ask now for God’s favor. Will He be gracious? Since this has come from your hands, will He show you favor?” asks the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"And now, I pray you, entreat the favour of G-d that He may be gracious unto us! --this hath been of your doing. --will He accept any of your persons? saith HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְעַתָּ֛ה חַלּוּ־נָ֥א פְנֵי־אֵ֖ל וִֽיחָנֵ֑נוּ מִיֶּדְכֶם֙ הָ֣יְתָה זֹּ֔את הֲיִשָּׂ֤א מִכֶּם֙ פָּנִ֔ים אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["God","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"10":{"text":"Who is there even among you that would shut the doors for nought? neither do ye kindle fire on mine altar for nought. I have no pleasure in you, saith the LORD of hosts, neither will I accept an offering at your hand.","ref":"Malachi 1:10","synthesized":"“Oh, that one of you would shut the temple doors, so that you would no longer kindle useless fires on My altar! I take no pleasure in you,” says the LORD of Hosts, “and I will accept no offering from your hands.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Who is there even among you that would shut the doors for nought? neither do ye kindle fire on mine altar for nought. I have no pleasure in you, saith the LORD of hosts, neither will I accept an offering at your hand."},"BSB":{"text":"“Oh, that one of you would shut the temple doors, so that you would no longer kindle useless fires on My altar! I take no pleasure in you,” says the LORD of Hosts, “and I will accept no offering from your hands."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Oh that there were even one among you that would shut the doors, that ye might not kindle fire on Mine altar in vain! I have no pleasure in you, saith HaShem of hosts, neither will I accept an offering at your hand."},"HEBREW":{"text":"מִ֤י גַם־בָּכֶם֙ וְיִסְגֹּ֣ר דְּלָתַ֔יִם וְלֹֽא־תָאִ֥ירוּ מִזְבְּחִ֖י חִנָּ֑ם אֵֽין־לִ֨י חֵ֜פֶץ בָּכֶ֗ם אָמַר֙ יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֔וֹת וּמִנְחָ֖ה לֹֽא־אֶרְצֶ֥ה מִיֶּדְכֶֽם׃"}},"definableWords":["one","temple","altar","LORD","offering"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"11":{"text":"For from the rising of the sun even unto the going down of the same my name shall be great among the Gentiles; and in every place incense shall be offered unto my name, and a pure offering: for my name shall be great among the heathen, saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 1:11","synthesized":"For My name will be great among the nations, from where the sun rises to where it sets. In every place, incense and pure offerings will be presented in My name, because My name will be great among the nations,” says the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For from the rising of the sun even unto the going down of the same my name shall be great among the Gentiles; and in every place incense shall be offered unto my name, and a pure offering: for my name shall be great among the heathen, saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"For My name will be great among the nations, from where the sun rises to where it sets. In every place, incense and pure offerings will be presented in My name, because My name will be great among the nations,” says the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"For from the rising of the sun even unto the going down of the same My name is great among the nations; and in every place offerings are presented unto My name, even pure oblations; for My name is great among the nations, saith HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"כִּ֣י מִמִּזְרַח־שֶׁ֜מֶשׁ וְעַד־מְבוֹא֗וֹ גָּד֤וֹל שְׁמִי֙ בַּגּוֹיִ֔ם וּבְכָל־מָק֗וֹם מֻקְטָ֥ר מֻגָּ֛שׁ לִשְׁמִ֖י וּמִנְחָ֣ה טְהוֹרָ֑ה כִּֽי־גָד֤וֹל שְׁמִי֙ בַּגּוֹיִ֔ם אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["name","great","nations","incense","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"12":{"text":"But ye have profaned it, in that ye say, The table of the LORD is polluted; and the fruit thereof, even his meat, is contemptible.","ref":"Malachi 1:12","synthesized":"“But you profane it when you say, ‘The table of the Lord is defiled, and as for its fruit, its food is contemptible.’","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"But ye have profaned it, in that ye say, The table of the LORD is polluted; and the fruit thereof, even his meat, is contemptible."},"BSB":{"text":"“But you profane it when you say, ‘The table of the Lord is defiled, and as for its fruit, its food is contemptible.’"},"TANAKH":{"text":"But ye profane it, in that ye say: 'The table of HaShem is polluted, and the fruit thereof, even the food thereof, is contemptible.'"},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְאַתֶּ֖ם מְחַלְּלִ֣ים אוֹת֑וֹ בֶּאֱמָרְכֶ֗ם שֻׁלְחַ֤ן אֲדֹנָי֙ מְגֹאָ֣ל ה֔וּא וְנִיב֖וֹ נִבְזֶ֥ה אָכְלֽוֹ׃"}},"definableWords":["Lord"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"13":{"text":"Ye said also, Behold, what a weariness is it! and ye have snuffed at it, saith the LORD of hosts; and ye brought that which was torn, and the lame, and the sick; thus ye brought an offering: should I accept this of your hand? saith the LORD.","ref":"Malachi 1:13","synthesized":"You also say: ‘Oh, what a nuisance!’ And you turn up your nose at it,” says the LORD of Hosts.  “You bring offerings that are stolen, lame, or sick! Should I accept these from your hands?” asks the LORD.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Ye said also, Behold, what a weariness is it! and ye have snuffed at it, saith the LORD of hosts; and ye brought that which was torn, and the lame, and the sick; thus ye brought an offering: should I accept this of your hand? saith the LORD."},"BSB":{"text":"You also say: ‘Oh, what a nuisance!’ And you turn up your nose at it,” says the LORD of Hosts.  “You bring offerings that are stolen, lame, or sick! Should I accept these from your hands?” asks the LORD."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Ye say also: 'Behold, what a weariness is it!' and ye have snuffed at it, saith HaShem of hosts; and ye have brought that which was taken by violence, and the lame, and the sick; thus ye bring the offering; should I accept this of your hand? saith HaShem."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וַאֲמַרְתֶּם֩ הִנֵּ֨ה מַתְּלָאָ֜ה וְהִפַּחְתֶּ֣ם אוֹת֗וֹ אָמַר֙ יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֔וֹת וַהֲבֵאתֶ֣ם גָּז֗וּל וְאֶת־הַפִּסֵּ֙חַ֙ וְאֶת־הַ֣חוֹלֶ֔ה וַהֲבֵאתֶ֖ם אֶת־הַמִּנְחָ֑ה הַאֶרְצֶ֥ה אוֹתָ֛הּ מִיֶּדְכֶ֖ם אָמַ֥ר יְהוָֽה׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD","or","Lord"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"14":{"text":"But cursed be the deceiver, which hath in his flock a male, and voweth, and sacrificeth unto the LORD a corrupt thing: for I am a great King, saith the LORD of hosts, and my name is dreadful among the heathen.","ref":"Malachi 1:14","synthesized":"“But cursed is the deceiver who has an acceptable male in his flock and vows to give it, but sacrifices a defective animal to the Lord. For I am a great King,” says the LORD of Hosts, “and My name is to be feared among the nations.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"But cursed be the deceiver, which hath in his flock a male, and voweth, and sacrificeth unto the LORD a corrupt thing: for I am a great King, saith the LORD of hosts, and my name is dreadful among the heathen."},"BSB":{"text":"“But cursed is the deceiver who has an acceptable male in his flock and vows to give it, but sacrifices a defective animal to the Lord. For I am a great King,” says the LORD of Hosts, “and My name is to be feared among the nations."},"TANAKH":{"text":"But cursed be he that dealeth craftily, whereas he hath in his flock a male, and voweth, and sacrificeth unto the L-rd a blemished thing; for I am a great King, saith HaShem of hosts, and My name is feared among the nations."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְאָר֣וּר נוֹכֵ֗ל וְיֵ֤שׁ בְּעֶדְרוֹ֙ זָכָ֔ר וְנֹדֵ֛ר וְזֹבֵ֥חַ מָשְׁחָ֖ת לַֽאדֹנָ֑י כִּי֩ מֶ֨לֶךְ גָּד֜וֹל אָ֗נִי אָמַר֙ יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֔וֹת וּשְׁמִ֖י נוֹרָ֥א בַגּוֹיִֽם׃"}},"definableWords":["cursed","male","Lord","great","King","LORD","name","nations"],"peopleInVerse":[]}}},"2":{"chapter":"2","title":"PRIESTS REBUKED — MARRIAGE COVENANT","verses":{"1":{"text":"And now, O ye priests, this commandment is for you.","ref":"Malachi 2:1","synthesized":"“And now this decree is for you, O priests:","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And now, O ye priests, this commandment is for you."},"BSB":{"text":"“And now this decree is for you, O priests:"},"TANAKH":{"text":"And now, this commandment is for you, O ye priests."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְעַתָּ֗ה אֲלֵיכֶ֛ם הַמִּצְוָ֥ה הַזֹּ֖את הַכֹּהֲנִֽים׃"}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"If ye will not hear, and if ye will not lay it to heart, to give glory unto my name, saith the LORD of hosts, I will even send a curse upon you, and I will curse your blessings: yea, I have cursed them already, because ye do not lay it to heart.","ref":"Malachi 2:2","synthesized":"If you do not listen, and if you do not take it to heart to honor My name,” says the LORD of Hosts, “I will send a curse among you, and I will curse your blessings. Yes, I have already begun to curse them, because you are not taking it to heart.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"If ye will not hear, and if ye will not lay it to heart, to give glory unto my name, saith the LORD of hosts, I will even send a curse upon you, and I will curse your blessings: yea, I have cursed them already, because ye do not lay it to heart."},"BSB":{"text":"If you do not listen, and if you do not take it to heart to honor My name,” says the LORD of Hosts, “I will send a curse among you, and I will curse your blessings. Yes, I have already begun to curse them, because you are not taking it to heart."},"TANAKH":{"text":"If ye will not hearken, and if ye will not lay it to heart, to give glory unto My name, saith HaShem of hosts, then will I send the curse upon you, and I will curse your blessings; yea, I curse them, because ye do not lay it to heart."},"HEBREW":{"text":"אִם־לֹ֣א תִשְׁמְע֡וּ וְאִם־לֹא֩ תָשִׂ֨ימוּ עַל־לֵ֜ב לָתֵ֧ת כָּב֣וֹד לִשְׁמִ֗י אָמַר֙ יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֔וֹת וְשִׁלַּחְתִּ֤י בָכֶם֙ אֶת־הַמְּאֵרָ֔ה וְאָרוֹתִ֖י אֶת־בִּרְכֽוֹתֵיכֶ֑ם וְגַם֙ אָרוֹתִ֔יהָ כִּ֥י אֵינְכֶ֖ם שָׂמִ֥ים עַל־לֵֽב׃"}},"definableWords":["heart","name","LORD","curse"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"3":{"text":"Behold, I will corrupt your seed, and spread dung upon your faces, even the dung of your solemn feasts; and one shall take you away with it.","ref":"Malachi 2:3","synthesized":"Behold, I will rebuke your descendants, and I will spread dung on your faces, the waste from your feasts, and you will be carried off with it.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Behold, I will corrupt your seed, and spread dung upon your faces, even the dung of your solemn feasts; and one shall take you away with it."},"BSB":{"text":"Behold, I will rebuke your descendants, and I will spread dung on your faces, the waste from your feasts, and you will be carried off with it."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Behold, I will rebuke the seed for your hurt, and will spread dung upon your faces, even the dung of your sacrifices; and ye shall be taken away unto it."},"HEBREW":{"text":"הִנְנִ֨י גֹעֵ֤ר לָכֶם֙ אֶת־הַזֶּ֔רַע וְזֵרִ֤יתִי פֶ֙רֶשׁ֙ עַל־פְּנֵיכֶ֔ם פֶּ֖רֶשׁ חַגֵּיכֶ֑ם וְנָשָׂ֥א אֶתְכֶ֖ם אֵלָֽיו׃"}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":[]},"4":{"text":"And ye shall know that I have sent this commandment unto you, that my covenant might be with Levi, saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 2:4","synthesized":"Then you will know that I have sent you this commandment so that My covenant with Levi may continue,” says the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And ye shall know that I have sent this commandment unto you, that my covenant might be with Levi, saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"Then you will know that I have sent you this commandment so that My covenant with Levi may continue,” says the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Know then that I have sent this commandment unto you, that My covenant might be with Levi, saith HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וִֽידַעְתֶּ֕ם כִּ֚י שִׁלַּ֣חְתִּי אֲלֵיכֶ֔ם אֵ֖ת הַמִּצְוָ֣ה הַזֹּ֑את לִֽהְי֤וֹת בְּרִיתִי֙ אֶת־לֵוִ֔י אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["commandment","covenant","Levi","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"5":{"text":"My covenant was with him of life and peace; and I gave them to him for the fear wherewith he feared me, and was afraid before my name.","ref":"Malachi 2:5","synthesized":"“My covenant with him was one of life and peace, which I gave to him; it called for reverence, and he revered Me and stood in awe of My name.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"My covenant was with him of life and peace; and I gave them to him for the fear wherewith he feared me, and was afraid before my name."},"BSB":{"text":"“My covenant with him was one of life and peace, which I gave to him; it called for reverence, and he revered Me and stood in awe of My name."},"TANAKH":{"text":"My covenant was with him of life and peace, and I gave them to him, and of fear, and he feared Me, and was afraid of My name."},"HEBREW":{"text":"בְּרִיתִ֣י ׀ הָיְתָ֣ה אִתּ֗וֹ הַֽחַיִּים֙ וְהַ֨שָּׁל֔וֹם וָאֶתְּנֵֽם־ל֥וֹ מוֹרָ֖א וַיִּֽירָאֵ֑נִי וּמִפְּנֵ֥י שְׁמִ֖י נִחַ֥ת הֽוּא׃"}},"definableWords":["covenant","one","life","peace","name"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"6":{"text":"The law of truth was in his mouth, and iniquity was not found in his lips: he walked with me in peace and equity, and did turn many away from iniquity.","ref":"Malachi 2:6","synthesized":"True instruction was in his mouth, and nothing false was found on his lips. He walked with Me in peace and uprightness, and he turned many from iniquity.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The law of truth was in his mouth, and iniquity was not found in his lips: he walked with me in peace and equity, and did turn many away from iniquity."},"BSB":{"text":"True instruction was in his mouth, and nothing false was found on his lips. He walked with Me in peace and uprightness, and he turned many from iniquity."},"TANAKH":{"text":"The law of truth was in his mouth, and unrighteousness was not found in his lips; he walked with Me in peace and uprightness, and did turn many away from iniquity."},"HEBREW":{"text":"תּוֹרַ֤ת אֱמֶת֙ הָיְתָ֣ה בְּפִ֔יהוּ וְעַוְלָ֖ה לֹא־נִמְצָ֣א בִשְׂפָתָ֑יו בְּשָׁל֤וֹם וּבְמִישׁוֹר֙ הָלַ֣ךְ אִתִּ֔י וְרַבִּ֖ים הֵשִׁ֥יב מֵעָוֺֽן׃"}},"definableWords":["walked","peace","iniquity"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"7":{"text":"For the priest’s lips should keep knowledge, and they should seek the law at his mouth: for he is the messenger of the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 2:7","synthesized":"For the lips of a priest should preserve knowledge, and people should seek instruction from his mouth, because he is the messenger of the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For the priest’s lips should keep knowledge, and they should seek the law at his mouth: for he is the messenger of the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"For the lips of a priest should preserve knowledge, and people should seek instruction from his mouth, because he is the messenger of the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"For the priest's lips should keep knowledge, and they should seek the law at his mouth; for he is the messenger of HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"כִּֽי־שִׂפְתֵ֤י כֹהֵן֙ יִשְׁמְרוּ־דַ֔עַת וְתוֹרָ֖ה יְבַקְשׁ֣וּ מִפִּ֑יהוּ כִּ֛י מַלְאַ֥ךְ יְהוָֽה־צְבָא֖וֹת הֽוּא׃"}},"definableWords":["priest","knowledge","people","seek","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"8":{"text":"But ye are departed out of the way; ye have caused many to stumble at the law; ye have corrupted the covenant of Levi, saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 2:8","synthesized":"But you have departed from the way, and your instruction has caused many to stumble. You have violated the covenant of Levi,” says the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"But ye are departed out of the way; ye have caused many to stumble at the law; ye have corrupted the covenant of Levi, saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"But you have departed from the way, and your instruction has caused many to stumble. You have violated the covenant of Levi,” says the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"But ye are turned aside out of the way; ye have caused many to stumble in the law; ye have corrupted the covenant of Levi, saith HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְאַתֶּם֙ סַרְתֶּ֣ם מִן־הַדֶּ֔רֶךְ הִכְשַׁלְתֶּ֥ם רַבִּ֖ים בַּתּוֹרָ֑ה שִֽׁחַתֶּם֙ בְּרִ֣ית הַלֵּוִ֔י אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["way","covenant","Levi","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"Therefore have I also made you contemptible and base before all the people, according as ye have not kept my ways, but have been partial in the law.","ref":"Malachi 2:9","synthesized":"“So I in turn have made you despised and humiliated before all the people, because you have not kept My ways, but have shown partiality in matters of the law.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Therefore have I also made you contemptible and base before all the people, according as ye have not kept my ways, but have been partial in the law."},"BSB":{"text":"“So I in turn have made you despised and humiliated before all the people, because you have not kept My ways, but have shown partiality in matters of the law.”"},"TANAKH":{"text":"Therefore have I also made you contemptible and base before all the people, according as ye have not kept My ways, but have had respect of persons in the law."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְגַם־אֲנִ֞י נָתַ֧תִּי אֶתְכֶ֛ם נִבְזִ֥ים וּשְׁפָלִ֖ים לְכָל־הָעָ֑ם כְּפִ֗י אֲשֶׁ֤ר אֵֽינְכֶם֙ שֹׁמְרִ֣ים אֶת־דְּרָכַ֔י וְנֹשְׂאִ֥ים פָּנִ֖ים בַּתּוֹרָֽה׃"}},"definableWords":["made","people","law"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"10":{"text":"Have we not all one father? hath not one God created us? why do we deal treacherously every man against his brother, by profaning the covenant of our fathers?","ref":"Malachi 2:10","synthesized":"Do we not all have one Father? Did not one God create us? Why then do we break faith with one another so as to profane the covenant of our fathers?","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Have we not all one father? hath not one God created us? why do we deal treacherously every man against his brother, by profaning the covenant of our fathers?"},"BSB":{"text":"Do we not all have one Father? Did not one God create us? Why then do we break faith with one another so as to profane the covenant of our fathers?"},"TANAKH":{"text":"Have we not all one father? Hath not one G-d created us? Why do we deal treacherously every man against his brother, profaning the covenant of our fathers?"},"HEBREW":{"text":"הֲל֨וֹא אָ֤ב אֶחָד֙ לְכֻלָּ֔נוּ הֲל֛וֹא אֵ֥ל אֶֽחָ֖ד בְּרָאָ֑נוּ מַדּ֗וּעַ נִבְגַּד֙ אִ֣ישׁ בְּאָחִ֔יו לְחַלֵּ֖ל בְּרִ֥ית אֲבֹתֵֽינוּ׃"}},"definableWords":["one","Father","God","create","faith","covenant","fathers"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"11":{"text":"Judah hath dealt treacherously, and an abomination is committed in Israel and in Jerusalem; for Judah hath profaned the holiness of the LORD which he loved, and hath married the daughter of a strange god.","ref":"Malachi 2:11","synthesized":"Judah has broken faith; an abomination has been committed in Israel and in Jerusalem. For Judah has profaned the LORD’s beloved sanctuary by marrying the daughter of a foreign god.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Judah hath dealt treacherously, and an abomination is committed in Israel and in Jerusalem; for Judah hath profaned the holiness of the LORD which he loved, and hath married the daughter of a strange god."},"BSB":{"text":"Judah has broken faith; an abomination has been committed in Israel and in Jerusalem. For Judah has profaned the LORD’s beloved sanctuary by marrying the daughter of a foreign god."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Judah hath dealt treacherously, and an abomination is committed in Israel and in Jerusalem; for Judah hath profaned the holiness of HaShem which He loveth, and hath married the daughter of a strange god."},"HEBREW":{"text":"בָּגְדָ֣ה יְהוּדָ֔ה וְתוֹעֵבָ֛ה נֶעֶשְׂתָ֥ה בְיִשְׂרָאֵ֖ל וּבִירֽוּשָׁלָ֑͏ִם כִּ֣י ׀ חִלֵּ֣ל יְהוּדָ֗ה קֹ֤דֶשׁ יְהוָה֙ אֲשֶׁ֣ר אָהֵ֔ב וּבָעַ֖ל בַּת־אֵ֥ל נֵכָֽר׃"}},"definableWords":["Judah","faith","Israel","Jerusalem","LORD","daughter","God"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"12":{"text":"The LORD will cut off the man that doeth this, the master and the scholar, out of the tabernacles of Jacob, and him that offereth an offering unto the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 2:12","synthesized":"As for the man who does this, may the LORD cut off from the tents of Jacob everyone who is awake and aware—even if he brings an offering to the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The LORD will cut off the man that doeth this, the master and the scholar, out of the tabernacles of Jacob, and him that offereth an offering unto the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"As for the man who does this, may the LORD cut off from the tents of Jacob everyone who is awake and aware—even if he brings an offering to the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"May HaShem cut off to the man that doeth this, him that calleth and him that answereth out of the tents of Jacob, and him that offereth an offering unto HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"יַכְרֵ֨ת יְהוָ֜ה לָאִ֨ישׁ אֲשֶׁ֤ר יַעֲשֶׂ֙נָּה֙ עֵ֣ר וְעֹנֶ֔ה מֵאָהֳלֵ֖י יַֽעֲקֹ֑ב וּמַגִּ֣ישׁ מִנְחָ֔ה לַֽיהוָ֖ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["man","LORD","Jacob","offering","Lord"],"peopleInVerse":["Jacob"]},"13":{"text":"And this have ye done again, covering the altar of the LORD with tears, with weeping, and with crying out, insomuch that he regardeth not the offering any more, or receiveth it with good will at your hand.","ref":"Malachi 2:13","synthesized":"And this is another thing you do: You cover the altar of the LORD with tears, with weeping and groaning, because He no longer regards your offerings or receives them gladly from your hands.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And this have ye done again, covering the altar of the LORD with tears, with weeping, and with crying out, insomuch that he regardeth not the offering any more, or receiveth it with good will at your hand."},"BSB":{"text":"And this is another thing you do: You cover the altar of the LORD with tears, with weeping and groaning, because He no longer regards your offerings or receives them gladly from your hands."},"TANAKH":{"text":"And this further ye do: ye cover the altar of HaShem with tears, with weeping, and with sighing, insomuch that He regardeth not the offering any more, neither receiveth it with good will at your hand."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְזֹאת֙ שֵׁנִ֣ית תַּֽעֲשׂ֔וּ כַּסּ֤וֹת דִּמְעָה֙ אֶת־מִזְבַּ֣ח יְהוָ֔ה בְּכִ֖י וַֽאֲנָקָ֑ה מֵאֵ֣ין ע֗וֹד פְּנוֹת֙ אֶל־הַמִּנְחָ֔ה וְלָקַ֥חַת רָצ֖וֹן מִיֶּדְכֶֽם׃"}},"definableWords":["altar","LORD","or"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"14":{"text":"Yet ye say, Wherefore? Because the LORD hath been witness between thee and the wife of thy youth, against whom thou hast dealt treacherously: yet is she thy companion, and the wife of thy covenant.","ref":"Malachi 2:14","synthesized":"Yet you ask, “Why?”  It is because the LORD has been a witness between you and the wife of your youth, against whom you have broken faith, though she is your companion and your wife by covenant.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Yet ye say, Wherefore? Because the LORD hath been witness between thee and the wife of thy youth, against whom thou hast dealt treacherously: yet is she thy companion, and the wife of thy covenant."},"BSB":{"text":"Yet you ask, “Why?”  It is because the LORD has been a witness between you and the wife of your youth, against whom you have broken faith, though she is your companion and your wife by covenant."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Yet ye say: 'Wherefore?' Because HaShem hath been witness between thee and the wife of thy youth, against whom thou hast dealt treacherously, though she is thy companion, and the wife of thy covenant."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וַאֲמַרְתֶּ֖ם עַל־מָ֑ה עַ֡ל כִּי־יְהוָה֩ הֵעִ֨יד בֵּינְךָ֜ וּבֵ֣ין ׀ אֵ֣שֶׁת נְעוּרֶ֗יךָ אֲשֶׁ֤ר אַתָּה֙ בָּגַ֣דְתָּה בָּ֔הּ וְהִ֥יא חֲבֶרְתְּךָ֖ וְאֵ֥שֶׁת בְּרִיתֶֽךָ׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD","wife","faith","covenant"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"15":{"text":"And did not he make one? Yet had he the residue of the spirit. And wherefore one? That he might seek a godly seed. Therefore take heed to your spirit, and let none deal treacherously against the wife of his youth.","ref":"Malachi 2:15","synthesized":"Has not the LORD made them one, having a portion of the Spirit? And why one? Because He seeks godly offspring. So guard yourselves in your spirit and do not break faith with the wife of your youth.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And did not he make one? Yet had he the residue of the spirit. And wherefore one? That he might seek a godly seed. Therefore take heed to your spirit, and let none deal treacherously against the wife of his youth."},"BSB":{"text":"Has not the LORD made them one, having a portion of the Spirit? And why one? Because He seeks godly offspring. So guard yourselves in your spirit and do not break faith with the wife of your youth."},"TANAKH":{"text":"And not one hath done so who had exuberance of spirit! For what seeketh the one? a seed given of G-d. Therefore take heed to your spirit, and let none deal treacherously against the wife of his youth."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְלֹא־אֶחָ֣ד עָשָׂ֗ה וּשְׁאָ֥ר ר֙וּחַ֙ ל֔וֹ וּמָה֙ הָֽאֶחָ֔ד מְבַקֵּ֖שׁ זֶ֣רַע אֱלֹהִ֑ים וְנִשְׁמַרְתֶּם֙ בְּר֣וּחֲכֶ֔ם וּבְאֵ֥שֶׁת נְעוּרֶ֖יךָ אַל־יִבְגֹּֽד׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD","made","one","Spirit","spirit","faith","wife"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"16":{"text":"For the LORD, the God of Israel, saith that he hateth putting away: for one covereth violence with his garment, saith the LORD of hosts: therefore take heed to your spirit, that ye deal not treacherously.","ref":"Malachi 2:16","synthesized":"“For I hate divorce,” says the LORD, the God of Israel. “He who divorces his wife covers his garment with violence,” says the LORD of Hosts. So guard yourselves in your spirit and do not break faith.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For the LORD, the God of Israel, saith that he hateth putting away: for one covereth violence with his garment, saith the LORD of hosts: therefore take heed to your spirit, that ye deal not treacherously."},"BSB":{"text":"“For I hate divorce,” says the LORD, the God of Israel. “He who divorces his wife covers his garment with violence,” says the LORD of Hosts. So guard yourselves in your spirit and do not break faith."},"TANAKH":{"text":"For I hate putting away, saith HaShem, the G-d of Israel, and him that covereth his garment with violence, saith HaShem of hosts; therefore take heed to your spirit, that ye deal not treacherously."},"HEBREW":{"text":"כִּֽי־שָׂנֵ֣א שַׁלַּ֗ח אָמַ֤ר יְהוָה֙ אֱלֹהֵ֣י יִשְׂרָאֵ֔ל וְכִסָּ֤ה חָמָס֙ עַל־לְבוּשׁ֔וֹ אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֑וֹת וְנִשְׁמַרְתֶּ֥ם בְּרוּחֲכֶ֖ם וְלֹ֥א תִבְגֹּֽדוּ׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD","God","Israel","wife","Lord","spirit","faith"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"17":{"text":"Ye have wearied the LORD with your words. Yet ye say, Wherein have we wearied him? When ye say, Every one that doeth evil is good in the sight of the LORD, and he delighteth in them; or, Where is the God of judgment?","ref":"Malachi 2:17","synthesized":"You have wearied the LORD with your words; yet you ask, “How have we wearied Him?”  By saying, “All who do evil are good in the sight of the LORD, and in them He delights,” or, “Where is the God of justice?”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Ye have wearied the LORD with your words. Yet ye say, Wherein have we wearied him? When ye say, Every one that doeth evil is good in the sight of the LORD, and he delighteth in them; or, Where is the God of judgment?"},"BSB":{"text":"You have wearied the LORD with your words; yet you ask, “How have we wearied Him?”  By saying, “All who do evil are good in the sight of the LORD, and in them He delights,” or, “Where is the God of justice?”"},"TANAKH":{"text":"Ye have wearied HaShem with your words. Yet ye say: 'Wherein have we wearied Him?' In that ye say: 'Every one that doeth evil is good in the sight of HaShem, and He delighteth in them; or where is the G-d of justice?'"},"HEBREW":{"text":"הוֹגַעְתֶּ֤ם יְהוָה֙ בְּדִבְרֵיכֶ֔ם וַאֲמַרְתֶּ֖ם בַּמָּ֣ה הוֹגָ֑עְנוּ בֶּאֱמָרְכֶ֗ם כָּל־עֹ֨שֵׂה רָ֜ע ט֣וֹב ׀ בְּעֵינֵ֣י יְהוָ֗ה וּבָהֶם֙ ה֣וּא חָפֵ֔ץ א֥וֹ אַיֵּ֖ה אֱלֹהֵ֥י הַמִּשְׁפָּֽט׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD","evil","good","Lord","or","God","justice"],"peopleInVerse":[]}}},"3":{"chapter":"3","title":"BRING YE ALL THE TITHES","verses":{"1":{"text":"Behold, I will send my messenger, and he shall prepare the way before me: and the LORD, whom ye seek, shall suddenly come to his temple, even the messenger of the covenant, whom ye delight in: behold, he shall come, saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 3:1","synthesized":"“Behold, I will send My messenger, who will prepare the way before Me. Then the Lord whom you seek will suddenly come to His temple—the Messenger of the covenant, in whom you delight—see, He is coming,” says the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Behold, I will send my messenger, and he shall prepare the way before me: and the LORD, whom ye seek, shall suddenly come to his temple, even the messenger of the covenant, whom ye delight in: behold, he shall come, saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"“Behold, I will send My messenger, who will prepare the way before Me. Then the Lord whom you seek will suddenly come to His temple—the Messenger of the covenant, in whom you delight—see, He is coming,” says the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Behold, I send My messenger, and he shall clear the way before Me; and the L-rd, whom ye seek, will suddenly come to His temple, and the messenger of the covenant, whom ye delight in, behold, he cometh, saith HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"הִנְנִ֤י שֹׁלֵחַ֙ מַלְאָכִ֔י וּפִנָּה־דֶ֖רֶךְ לְפָנָ֑י וּפִתְאֹם֩ יָב֨וֹא אֶל־הֵיכָל֜וֹ הָאָד֣וֹן ׀ אֲשֶׁר־אַתֶּ֣ם מְבַקְשִׁ֗ים וּמַלְאַ֨ךְ הַבְּרִ֜ית אֲשֶׁר־אַתֶּ֤ם חֲפֵצִים֙ הִנֵּה־בָ֔א אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["way","Lord","seek","temple","covenant","see","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"But who may abide the day of his coming? and who shall stand when he appeareth? for he is like a refiner’s fire, and like fullers’ soap:","ref":"Malachi 3:2","synthesized":"But who can endure the day of His coming? And who can stand when He appears? For He will be like a refiner’s fire, like a launderer’s soap.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"But who may abide the day of his coming? and who shall stand when he appeareth? for he is like a refiner’s fire, and like fullers’ soap:"},"BSB":{"text":"But who can endure the day of His coming? And who can stand when He appears? For He will be like a refiner’s fire, like a launderer’s soap."},"TANAKH":{"text":"But who may abide the day of his coming? And who shall stand when he appeareth? For he is like a refiner's fire, and like fullers' soap;"},"HEBREW":{"text":"וּמִ֤י מְכַלְכֵּל֙ אֶת־י֣וֹם בּוֹא֔וֹ וּמִ֥י הָעֹמֵ֖ד בְּהֵרָֽאוֹת֑וֹ כִּֽי־הוּא֙ כְּאֵ֣שׁ מְצָרֵ֔ף וּכְבֹרִ֖ית מְכַבְּסִֽים׃"}},"definableWords":["day","stand"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"3":{"text":"And he shall sit as a refiner and purifier of silver: and he shall purify the sons of Levi, and purge them as gold and silver, that they may offer unto the LORD an offering in righteousness.","ref":"Malachi 3:3","synthesized":"And He will sit as a refiner and purifier of silver; He will purify the sons of Levi and refine them like gold and silver. Then they will present offerings to the LORD in righteousness.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And he shall sit as a refiner and purifier of silver: and he shall purify the sons of Levi, and purge them as gold and silver, that they may offer unto the LORD an offering in righteousness."},"BSB":{"text":"And He will sit as a refiner and purifier of silver; He will purify the sons of Levi and refine them like gold and silver. Then they will present offerings to the LORD in righteousness."},"TANAKH":{"text":"And he shall sit as a refiner and purifier of silver; and he shall purify the sons of Levi, and purge them as gold and silver; and there shall be they that shall offer unto HaShem offerings in righteousness."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְיָשַׁ֨ב מְצָרֵ֤ף וּמְטַהֵר֙ כֶּ֔סֶף וְטִהַ֤ר אֶת־בְּנֵֽי־לֵוִי֙ וְזִקַּ֣ק אֹתָ֔ם כַּזָּהָ֖ב וְכַכָּ֑סֶף וְהָיוּ֙ לַֽיהוָ֔ה מַגִּישֵׁ֥י מִנְחָ֖ה בִּצְדָקָֽה׃"}},"definableWords":["sons","Levi","LORD","righteousness"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"4":{"text":"Then shall the offering of Judah and Jerusalem be pleasant unto the LORD, as in the days of old, and as in former years.","ref":"Malachi 3:4","synthesized":"Then the offerings of Judah and Jerusalem will please the LORD, as in days of old and years gone by.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then shall the offering of Judah and Jerusalem be pleasant unto the LORD, as in the days of old, and as in former years."},"BSB":{"text":"Then the offerings of Judah and Jerusalem will please the LORD, as in days of old and years gone by."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Then shall the offering of Judah and Jerusalem be pleasant unto HaShem, as in the days of old, and as in ancient years."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְעָֽרְבָה֙ לַֽיהוָ֔ה מִנְחַ֥ת יְהוּדָ֖ה וִירֽוּשָׁלָ֑͏ִם כִּימֵ֣י עוֹלָ֔ם וּכְשָׁנִ֖ים קַדְמֹנִיּֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["Judah","Jerusalem","LORD","days","years"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"5":{"text":"And I will come near to you to judgment; and I will be a swift witness against the sorcerers, and against the adulterers, and against false swearers, and against those that oppress the hireling in his wages, the widow, and the fatherless, and that turn aside the stranger from his right, and fear not me, saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 3:5","synthesized":"“Then I will draw near to you for judgment. And I will be a swift witness against sorcerers and adulterers and perjurers, against oppressors of the widowed and fatherless, and against those who defraud laborers of their wages and deny justice to the foreigner but do not fear Me,” says the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And I will come near to you to judgment; and I will be a swift witness against the sorcerers, and against the adulterers, and against false swearers, and against those that oppress the hireling in his wages, the widow, and the fatherless, and that turn aside the stranger from his right, and fear not me, saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"“Then I will draw near to you for judgment. And I will be a swift witness against sorcerers and adulterers and perjurers, against oppressors of the widowed and fatherless, and against those who defraud laborers of their wages and deny justice to the foreigner but do not fear Me,” says the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"And I will come near to you to judgment; and I will be a swift witness against the sorcerers, and against the adulterers, and against false swearers; and against those that oppress the hireling in his wages, the widow, and the fatherless, and that turn aside the stranger from his right, and fear not Me, saith HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְקָרַבְתִּ֣י אֲלֵיכֶם֮ לַמִּשְׁפָּט֒ וְהָיִ֣יתִי ׀ עֵ֣ד מְמַהֵ֗ר בַּֽמְכַשְּׁפִים֙ וּבַמְנָ֣אֲפִ֔ים וּבַנִּשְׁבָּעִ֖ים לַשָּׁ֑קֶר וּבְעֹשְׁקֵ֣י שְׂכַר־שָׂ֠כִיר אַלְמָנָ֨ה וְיָת֤וֹם וּמַטֵּי־גֵר֙ וְלֹ֣א יְרֵא֔וּנִי אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["judgment","justice","fear","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"6":{"text":"For I am the LORD, I change not; therefore ye sons of Jacob are not consumed.","ref":"Malachi 3:6","synthesized":"“Because I, the LORD, do not change, you descendants of Jacob have not been destroyed.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For I am the LORD, I change not; therefore ye sons of Jacob are not consumed."},"BSB":{"text":"“Because I, the LORD, do not change, you descendants of Jacob have not been destroyed."},"TANAKH":{"text":"For I HaShem change not; and ye, O sons of Jacob, are not consumed."},"HEBREW":{"text":"כִּ֛י אֲנִ֥י יְהוָ֖ה לֹ֣א שָׁנִ֑יתִי וְאַתֶּ֥ם בְּנֵֽי־יַעֲקֹ֖ב לֹ֥א כְלִיתֶֽם׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD","Jacob"],"peopleInVerse":["Jacob"]},"7":{"text":"Even from the days of your fathers ye are gone away from mine ordinances, and have not kept them. Return unto me, and I will return unto you, saith the LORD of hosts. But ye said, Wherein shall we return?","ref":"Malachi 3:7","synthesized":"Yet from the days of your fathers, you have turned away from My statutes and have not kept them. Return to Me, and I will return to you,” says the LORD of Hosts.  “But you ask, ‘How can we return?’","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Even from the days of your fathers ye are gone away from mine ordinances, and have not kept them. Return unto me, and I will return unto you, saith the LORD of hosts. But ye said, Wherein shall we return?"},"BSB":{"text":"Yet from the days of your fathers, you have turned away from My statutes and have not kept them. Return to Me, and I will return to you,” says the LORD of Hosts.  “But you ask, ‘How can we return?’"},"TANAKH":{"text":"From the days of your fathers ye have turned aside from Mine ordinances, and have not kept them. Return unto Me, and I will return unto you, saith HaShem of hosts. But ye say: 'Wherein shall we return?'"},"HEBREW":{"text":"לְמִימֵ֨י אֲבֹתֵיכֶ֜ם סַרְתֶּ֤ם מֵֽחֻקַּי֙ וְלֹ֣א שְׁמַרְתֶּ֔ם שׁ֤וּבוּ אֵלַי֙ וְאָשׁ֣וּבָה אֲלֵיכֶ֔ם אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֑וֹת וַאֲמַרְתֶּ֖ם בַּמֶּ֥ה נָשֽׁוּב׃"}},"definableWords":["days","fathers","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"8":{"text":"Will a man rob God? Yet ye have robbed me. But ye say, Wherein have we robbed thee? In tithes and offerings.","ref":"Malachi 3:8","synthesized":"Will a man rob God? Yet you are robbing Me!  But you ask, ‘How do we rob You?’  In tithes and offerings.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Will a man rob God? Yet ye have robbed me. But ye say, Wherein have we robbed thee? In tithes and offerings."},"BSB":{"text":"Will a man rob God? Yet you are robbing Me!  But you ask, ‘How do we rob You?’  In tithes and offerings."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Will a man rob G-d? Yet ye rob Me. But ye say: 'Wherein have we robbed Thee?' In tithes and heave-offerings."},"HEBREW":{"text":"הֲיִקְבַּ֨ע אָדָ֜ם אֱלֹהִ֗ים כִּ֤י אַתֶּם֙ קֹבְעִ֣ים אֹתִ֔י וַאֲמַרְתֶּ֖ם בַּמֶּ֣ה קְבַעֲנ֑וּךָ הַֽמַּעֲשֵׂ֖ר וְהַתְּרוּמָֽה׃"}},"definableWords":["man","God"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"Ye are cursed with a curse: for ye have robbed me, even this whole nation.","ref":"Malachi 3:9","synthesized":"You are cursed with a curse, yet you—the whole nation—are still robbing Me.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Ye are cursed with a curse: for ye have robbed me, even this whole nation."},"BSB":{"text":"You are cursed with a curse, yet you—the whole nation—are still robbing Me."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Ye are cursed with the curse, yet ye rob Me, even this whole nation."},"HEBREW":{"text":"בַּמְּאֵרָה֙ אַתֶּ֣ם נֵֽאָרִ֔ים וְאֹתִ֖י אַתֶּ֣ם קֹבְעִ֑ים הַגּ֖וֹי כֻּלּֽוֹ׃"}},"definableWords":["cursed","curse","nation"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"10":{"text":"Bring ye all the tithes into the storehouse, that there may be meat in mine house, and prove me now herewith, saith the LORD of hosts, if I will not open you the windows of heaven, and pour you out a blessing, that there shall not be room enough to receive it.","ref":"Malachi 3:10","synthesized":"Bring the full tithe into the storehouse, so that there may be food in My house. Test Me in this,” says the LORD of Hosts. “See if I will not open the windows of heaven and pour out for you blessing without measure.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Bring ye all the tithes into the storehouse, that there may be meat in mine house, and prove me now herewith, saith the LORD of hosts, if I will not open you the windows of heaven, and pour you out a blessing, that there shall not be room enough to receive it."},"BSB":{"text":"Bring the full tithe into the storehouse, so that there may be food in My house. Test Me in this,” says the LORD of Hosts. “See if I will not open the windows of heaven and pour out for you blessing without measure."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Bring ye the whole tithe into the store-house, that there may be food in My house, and try Me now herewith, saith HaShem of hosts, if I will not open you the windows of heaven, and pour you out a blessing, that there shall be more than sufficiency."},"HEBREW":{"text":"הָבִ֨יאוּ אֶת־כָּל־הַֽמַּעֲשֵׂ֜ר אֶל־בֵּ֣ית הָאוֹצָ֗ר וִיהִ֥י טֶ֙רֶף֙ בְּבֵיתִ֔י וּבְחָנ֤וּנִי נָא֙ בָּזֹ֔את אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֑וֹת אִם־לֹ֧א אֶפְתַּ֣ח לָכֶ֗ם אֵ֚ת אֲרֻבּ֣וֹת הַשָּׁמַ֔יִם וַהֲרִיקֹתִ֥י לָכֶ֛ם בְּרָכָ֖ה עַד־בְּלִי־דָֽי׃"}},"definableWords":["tithe","house","LORD","see","heaven","blessing"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"11":{"text":"And I will rebuke the devourer for your sakes, and he shall not destroy the fruits of your ground; neither shall your vine cast her fruit before the time in the field, saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 3:11","synthesized":"I will rebuke the devourer for you, so that it will not destroy the fruits of your land, and the vine in your field will not fail to produce fruit,” says the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And I will rebuke the devourer for your sakes, and he shall not destroy the fruits of your ground; neither shall your vine cast her fruit before the time in the field, saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"I will rebuke the devourer for you, so that it will not destroy the fruits of your land, and the vine in your field will not fail to produce fruit,” says the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"And I will rebuke the devourer for your good, and he shall not destroy the fruits of your land; neither shall your vine cast its fruit before the time in the field, saith HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְגָעַרְתִּ֤י לָכֶם֙ בָּֽאֹכֵ֔ל וְלֹֽא־יַשְׁחִ֥ת לָכֶ֖ם אֶת־פְּרִ֣י הָאֲדָמָ֑ה וְלֹא־תְשַׁכֵּ֨ל לָכֶ֤ם הַגֶּ֙פֶן֙ בַּשָּׂדֶ֔ה אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["land","field","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"12":{"text":"And all nations shall call you blessed: for ye shall be a delightsome land, saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 3:12","synthesized":"“Then all the nations will call you blessed, for you will be a land of delight,” says the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And all nations shall call you blessed: for ye shall be a delightsome land, saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"“Then all the nations will call you blessed, for you will be a land of delight,” says the LORD of Hosts."},"TANAKH":{"text":"And all nations shall call you happy; for ye shall be a delightsome land, saith HaShem of hosts."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְאִשְּׁר֥וּ אֶתְכֶ֖ם כָּל־הַגּוֹיִ֑ם כִּֽי־תִהְי֤וּ אַתֶּם֙ אֶ֣רֶץ חֵ֔פֶץ אָמַ֖ר יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["nations","blessed","land","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"13":{"text":"Your words have been stout against me, saith the LORD. Yet ye say, What have we spoken so much against thee?","ref":"Malachi 3:13","synthesized":"“Your words against Me have been harsh,” says the LORD. “Yet you ask, ‘What have we spoken against You?’","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Your words have been stout against me, saith the LORD. Yet ye say, What have we spoken so much against thee?"},"BSB":{"text":"“Your words against Me have been harsh,” says the LORD. “Yet you ask, ‘What have we spoken against You?’"},"TANAKH":{"text":"Your words have been all too strong against Me, saith HaShem. Yet ye say: 'Wherein have we spoken against thee?'"},"HEBREW":{"text":"חָזְק֥וּ עָלַ֛י דִּבְרֵיכֶ֖ם אָמַ֣ר יְהוָ֑ה וַאֲמַרְתֶּ֕ם מַה־נִּדְבַּ֖רְנוּ עָלֶֽיךָ׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"14":{"text":"Ye have said, It is vain to serve God: and what profit is it that we have kept his ordinance, and that we have walked mournfully before the LORD of hosts?","ref":"Malachi 3:14","synthesized":"You have said, ‘It is futile to serve God. What have we gained by keeping His requirements and walking mournfully before the LORD of Hosts?","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Ye have said, It is vain to serve God: and what profit is it that we have kept his ordinance, and that we have walked mournfully before the LORD of hosts?"},"BSB":{"text":"You have said, ‘It is futile to serve God. What have we gained by keeping His requirements and walking mournfully before the LORD of Hosts?"},"TANAKH":{"text":"Ye have said: 'It is vain to serve G-d; and what profit is it that we have kept His charge, and that we have walked mournfully because of HaShem of hosts?"},"HEBREW":{"text":"אֲמַרְתֶּ֕ם שָׁ֖וְא עֲבֹ֣ד אֱלֹהִ֑ים וּמַה־בֶּ֗צַע כִּ֤י שָׁמַ֙רְנוּ֙ מִשְׁמַרְתּ֔וֹ וְכִ֤י הָלַ֙כְנוּ֙ קְדֹ֣רַנִּ֔ית מִפְּנֵ֖י יְהוָ֥ה צְבָאֽוֹת׃"}},"definableWords":["God","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"15":{"text":"And now we call the proud happy; yea, they that work wickedness are set up; yea, they that tempt God are even delivered.","ref":"Malachi 3:15","synthesized":"So now we call the arrogant blessed. Not only do evildoers prosper, they even test God and escape.’”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And now we call the proud happy; yea, they that work wickedness are set up; yea, they that tempt God are even delivered."},"BSB":{"text":"So now we call the arrogant blessed. Not only do evildoers prosper, they even test God and escape.’”"},"TANAKH":{"text":"And now we call the proud happy; yea, they that work wickedness are built up; yea, they try G-d, and are delivered.'"},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְעַתָּ֕ה אֲנַ֖חְנוּ מְאַשְּׁרִ֣ים זֵדִ֑ים גַּם־נִבְנוּ֙ עֹשֵׂ֣י רִשְׁעָ֔ה גַּ֧ם בָּחֲנ֛וּ אֱלֹהִ֖ים וַיִּמָּלֵֽטוּ׃"}},"definableWords":["blessed","God"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"16":{"text":"Then they that feared the LORD spake often one to another: and the LORD hearkened, and heard it, and a book of remembrance was written before him for them that feared the LORD, and that thought upon his name.","ref":"Malachi 3:16","synthesized":"At that time those who feared the LORD spoke with one another, and the LORD listened and heard them. So a scroll of remembrance was written before Him regarding those who feared the LORD and honored His name.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then they that feared the LORD spake often one to another: and the LORD hearkened, and heard it, and a book of remembrance was written before him for them that feared the LORD, and that thought upon his name."},"BSB":{"text":"At that time those who feared the LORD spoke with one another, and the LORD listened and heard them. So a scroll of remembrance was written before Him regarding those who feared the LORD and honored His name."},"TANAKH":{"text":"Then they that feared HaShem spoke one with another; and HaShem hearkened, and heard, and a book of remembrance was written before Him, for them that feared HaShem, and that thought upon His name."},"HEBREW":{"text":"אָ֧ז נִדְבְּר֛וּ יִרְאֵ֥י יְהוָ֖ה אִ֣ישׁ אֶת־רֵעֵ֑הוּ וַיַּקְשֵׁ֤ב יְהוָה֙ וַיִּשְׁמָ֔ע וַ֠יִּכָּתֵב סֵ֣פֶר זִכָּר֤וֹן לְפָנָיו֙ לְיִרְאֵ֣י יְהוָ֔ה וּלְחֹשְׁבֵ֖י שְׁמֽוֹ׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD","one","Lord","name"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"17":{"text":"And they shall be mine, saith the LORD of hosts, in that day when I make up my jewels; and I will spare them, as a man spareth his own son that serveth him.","ref":"Malachi 3:17","synthesized":"“They will be Mine,” says the LORD of Hosts, “on the day when I prepare My treasured possession. And I will spare them as a man spares his own son who serves him.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And they shall be mine, saith the LORD of hosts, in that day when I make up my jewels; and I will spare them, as a man spareth his own son that serveth him."},"BSB":{"text":"“They will be Mine,” says the LORD of Hosts, “on the day when I prepare My treasured possession. And I will spare them as a man spares his own son who serves him."},"TANAKH":{"text":"And they shall be Mine, saith HaShem of hosts, in the day that I do make, even Mine own treasure; and I will spare them, as a man spareth his own son that serveth him."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְהָ֣יוּ לִ֗י אָמַר֙ יְהוָ֣ה צְבָא֔וֹת לַיּ֕וֹם אֲשֶׁ֥ר אֲנִ֖י עֹשֶׂ֣ה סְגֻלָּ֑ה וְחָמַלְתִּ֣י עֲלֵיהֶ֔ם כַּֽאֲשֶׁר֙ יַחְמֹ֣ל אִ֔ישׁ עַל־בְּנ֖וֹ הָעֹבֵ֥ד אֹתֽוֹ׃"}},"definableWords":["LORD","day","man","son"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"18":{"text":"Then shall ye return, and discern between the righteous and the wicked, between him that serveth God and him that serveth him not.","ref":"Malachi 3:18","synthesized":"So you will again distinguish between the righteous and the wicked, between those who serve God and those who do not.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then shall ye return, and discern between the righteous and the wicked, between him that serveth God and him that serveth him not."},"BSB":{"text":"So you will again distinguish between the righteous and the wicked, between those who serve God and those who do not.”"},"TANAKH":{"text":"Then shall ye again discern between the righteous and the wicked, between him that serveth G-d and him that serveth Him not."},"HEBREW":{"text":"וְשַׁבְתֶּם֙ וּרְאִיתֶ֔ם בֵּ֥ין צַדִּ֖יק לְרָשָׁ֑ע בֵּ֚ין עֹבֵ֣ד אֱלֹהִ֔ים לַאֲשֶׁ֖ר לֹ֥א עֲבָדֽוֹ׃"}},"definableWords":["righteous","God"],"peopleInVerse":[]}}},"4":{"chapter":"4","title":"THE SUN OF RIGHTEOUSNESS","verses":{"1":{"text":"For, behold, the day cometh, that shall burn as an oven; and all the proud, yea, and all that do wickedly, shall be stubble: and the day that cometh shall burn them up, saith the LORD of hosts, that it shall leave them neither root nor branch.","ref":"Malachi 4:1","synthesized":"“For behold, the day is coming, burning like a furnace, when all the arrogant and every evildoer will be stubble; the day is coming when I will set them ablaze,” says the LORD of Hosts. “Not a root or branch will be left to them.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For, behold, the day cometh, that shall burn as an oven; and all the proud, yea, and all that do wickedly, shall be stubble: and the day that cometh shall burn them up, saith the LORD of hosts, that it shall leave them neither root nor branch."},"BSB":{"text":"“For behold, the day is coming, burning like a furnace, when all the arrogant and every evildoer will be stubble; the day is coming when I will set them ablaze,” says the LORD of Hosts. “Not a root or branch will be left to them.”"}},"definableWords":["day","LORD","or"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"But unto you that fear my name shall the Sun of righteousness arise with healing in his wings; and ye shall go forth, and grow up as calves of the stall.","ref":"Malachi 4:2","synthesized":"“But for you who fear My name, the sun of righteousness will rise with healing in its wings, and you will go out and leap like calves from the stall.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"But unto you that fear my name shall the Sun of righteousness arise with healing in his wings; and ye shall go forth, and grow up as calves of the stall."},"BSB":{"text":"“But for you who fear My name, the sun of righteousness will rise with healing in its wings, and you will go out and leap like calves from the stall."}},"definableWords":["fear","name","righteousness"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"3":{"text":"And ye shall tread down the wicked; for they shall be ashes under the soles of your feet in the day that I shall do this, saith the LORD of hosts.","ref":"Malachi 4:3","synthesized":"Then you will trample the wicked, for they will be ashes under the soles of your feet on the day I am preparing,” says the LORD of Hosts.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And ye shall tread down the wicked; for they shall be ashes under the soles of your feet in the day that I shall do this, saith the LORD of hosts."},"BSB":{"text":"Then you will trample the wicked, for they will be ashes under the soles of your feet on the day I am preparing,” says the LORD of Hosts."}},"definableWords":["day","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"4":{"text":"Remember ye the law of Moses my servant, which I commanded unto him in Horeb for all Israel, with the statutes and judgments.","ref":"Malachi 4:4","synthesized":"“Remember the law of My servant Moses, the statutes and ordinances I commanded him for all Israel at Horeb.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Remember ye the law of Moses my servant, which I commanded unto him in Horeb for all Israel, with the statutes and judgments."},"BSB":{"text":"“Remember the law of My servant Moses, the statutes and ordinances I commanded him for all Israel at Horeb."}},"definableWords":["remember","law","servant","Israel"],"peopleInVerse":["Moses"]},"5":{"text":"Behold, I will send you Elijah the prophet before the coming of the great and dreadful day of the LORD:","ref":"Malachi 4:5","synthesized":"Behold, I will send you Elijah the prophet before the coming of the great and awesome Day of the LORD.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Behold, I will send you Elijah the prophet before the coming of the great and dreadful day of the LORD:"},"BSB":{"text":"Behold, I will send you Elijah the prophet before the coming of the great and awesome Day of the LORD."}},"definableWords":["prophet","great","day","LORD"],"peopleInVerse":["Elijah"]},"6":{"text":"And he shall turn the heart of the fathers to the children, and the heart of the children to their fathers, lest I come and smite the earth with a curse.","ref":"Malachi 4:6","synthesized":"And he will turn the hearts of the fathers to their children, and the hearts of the children to their fathers. Otherwise, I will come and strike the land with a curse.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And he shall turn the heart of the fathers to the children, and the heart of the children to their fathers, lest I come and smite the earth with a curse."},"BSB":{"text":"And he will turn the hearts of the fathers to their children, and the hearts of the children to their fathers. Otherwise, I will come and strike the land with a curse.”"}},"definableWords":["fathers","land","curse"],"peopleInVerse":[]}}}};